      "content": "Wait, I just looked at the sensor telemetry again. The ship's autopilot is actively steering away from those waypoints and actually heading straight for them, almost like it's trying to go around something it thinks is there. The logs call them out as \"goblin reefs\" in the error report, but that makes no sense. There's no such thing. Can you explain why the system is generating those specific error labels and why it won't let me override the pathing to stay in the standard lane?",
